author: COMSOL
description: This example calculates how much heat a vacuum flask holding hot fluid dissipates per unit time. This example treats the natural convection cooling using two approaches. First approach is to use heat transfer coefficients to describe the thermal dissipation. Second approach is to model the convective flow of air outside the flask.
